\par\pard\plain \li400\fi360\ri400\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 An appeal to the life of Abraham is ideally suited for these purposes. He is indeed an object lesson of the main truth that Paul is explaining in these chapters, i.e., that God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s way of saving sinners is by grace, which means that we are justified by faith apart from works of law. Paul sees }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ge15.6"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Gen 15:6}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  as a summary statement of this truth, and }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Romans 4}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  is basically an exposition of this verse.}
