\par\pard\plain \li400\fi360\ri400\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The content of this section seems to fall into six paragraphs, thus: Abraham was justified by faith apart from works (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.1-5"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:1\endash 5}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). This is explained and confirmed by David in }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ps32.1-2"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Ps 32:1\endash 2}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.6-8"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:6\endash 8}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). Membership in Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s family is by faith, not by circumcision; thus Abraham is the spiritual father of both believing Gentiles and believing Jews (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.9-12"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:9\endash 12}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). The inheritance promised to Abraham comes by faith, not by law or works of law (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.13-17a"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:13\endash 17a}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). Abraham shows us what this justifying faith is like: it means giving glory to God and believing his promises (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.17b-22"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:17b\endash 22}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). Finally, all this is relevant for Christians today because anyone who believes like Abraham will be justified like Abraham (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.23-25"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:23\endash 25}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ).}
