\par\pard\plain \li400\ri400\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As the focus of his faith, Abraham believed that God could miraculously restore both his and Sarah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s reproductive powers, a kind of figurative \u8220\'93resurrection from the dead\u8221\'94 (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.19"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:19}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Heb11.11-12"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Heb 11:11\endash 12}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). He also believed that God had the power to raise Isaac from the dead if necessary, had the commanded sacrifice been completed (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Heb11.19"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Heb 11:19}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). This sets the example for us, who are called on to believe that God raised Jesus from the dead (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.24"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:24}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ), and to believe that he raises us from spiritual death in baptism (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro6.4"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 6:4}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Col2.12"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Col 2:12}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ) and will raise us up from physical death on the last day (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro8.11"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 8:11}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro8.23"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 23}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ).}
