\par\pard\plain \li400\fi360\ri400\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Under such circumstances Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s hope surely transcended all expectation based on natural processes (his own \u8220\'93works\u8221\'94); it was surely grounded in his faith that God could raise the dead and bring something out of nothing. Paul says it thus, that Abraham believed \u8220\'93against all hope,\u8221\'94 yet \u8220\'93in hope.\u8221\'94}
