\par\pard\plain \li400\fi360\ri400\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The act of faith is here called believing \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93upon\u8221\'94 (}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u7952\'3F\u960\'70\u943\'3F}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , }{\f4\fs24\b0\i1 epi}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ), which is not just bare intellectual assent to facts but also a surrender of the will and a commitment of the self to the }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 person}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  who is the object of faith, in this case God the Father. In the context of salvation Jesus is usually named as the object of faith (e.g., }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Jn3.16"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 John 3:16}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ac11.17"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Acts 11:17}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ac16.31"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 16:31}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro3.22"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Rom 3:22}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ga2.16"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Gal 2:16}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ga3.26"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 3:26}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ), but not exclusively so (see }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ac16.34"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Acts 16:34}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.5"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Rom 4:5}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Col2.12"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Col 2:12}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 )}
