\par\pard\plain \li400\fi360\ri400\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 It is clear that justifying faith must include faith in the resurrection of Jesus from the dead (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro10.9"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 10:9}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ), in addition to faith in the atoning power of his death (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro3.25"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 3:25}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). Abraham\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s faith is most appropriately paradigmatic for the former, since it was truly a faith that God is able to raise the dead (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.17"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 4:17}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ro4.19"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 19}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). Our faith is no different, except we now know that this holy resurrection power is ultimately displayed in the raising of Jesus (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Eph1.18-20"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Eph 1:18\endash 20}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Col2.12"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Col 2:12}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ). In this light it is significant that the final fulfilment of God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s promise to Abraham was when he raised Jesus from the dead (}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosref/Bible.Ac13.32-34"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf3 Acts 13:32\endash 34}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ).}
